<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="761" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="53.[1994,2591,1977,2405]" lastBlockId="53.[1385,2591,2411,3075]" pageId="53" pageNumber="761">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1996,2276,2174,2207]" pageId="53" pageNumber="761">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 173-205 mm, tail 175-192 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. Dorsal hair of the Mentawai Flying Squirrel is dark brown, with even darker, slightly distichous tail. Underparts are paler light slate-gray; outer edges of limbs and patagium are grizzled with buff hairs. Ears are naked. Females have two pairs of inguinal nipples.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1385,2247,2490,2523]" pageId="53" pageNumber="761" type="biology_ecology">
